latestIgtvVideos.title: Pyaar ka Nagma
latestIgtvVideos.caption:
Let me just put it out there. I love the sari. 
This versatile piece of 6 yards (or 9), transcends socio-economic divisions and can be worn in at least a 100 ways. I know only one! I lament about the complexity of draping one, but it's actually super easy. And of course, practice helps.
For me, it's an empowering garment and a way to connect with my Indian heritage.

And so I made a small video montage of it. 😛 I hope you'll like it.. 💕💕 Thank youu @shilpabhawnani for lending your beautiful voice on the ukelele for this. It's the soul of this video I'd say. 
Do let me know if you liked it! 😁

p.s. my friends are amaaaze

latestIgtvVideos.title: An Ode to Bangalore
latestIgtvVideos.caption:
So @phalgunkp and I set out on a chilly Bangalore evening to get some pictures on 35mm film. Intentionally AND unintentionally we also ended up making a montage of sorts of our day around, hopping on and off metro trains, buildings, alleys and ofcourse, Brigade road. 
I have spent incopious amounts of time in the metro and in-n-around Brigade road...so I think this is an ode to the beautiful times in my city. An ode to Bangalore.

Thank you @phalgunkp for your energy. 
#bangaloremylove

latestPosts.caption:
Roughly been one year since this magical experience. Each day I go on to apply and practice more of what @cocorocha taught us. 
I see it now, over the course of a year, how my learnings at model camp has impacted the quality of my work.

I did have a few skills beforehand, everything that I'd learnt up till then, all by seeing and observing models whose work I liked. But they were all over the place. 
What @cocorocha at @cocorochamodelcamp did was hone those skills and give me tools to build upon that foundation of knowledge. And it has made all the difference. 🤩

In the video Coco is cheering me on and she says 'I'm so proud of you' and I could have legit cried when she said that. 😭 
Whatever you do, it's never a bad idea to invest in the knowledge you seek. ❤
_

latestPosts.caption:
You’ll be disappointed. The answer is nothing fancy. I’m training for…life. That’s the answer. Life.
Healthy life. Disease free life. 
Ageing-gracefully-life. 
Independent-into-my-90s-life.

My biggest fitness goal is longevity. Aesthetics matter right now yes, especially for my profession, but I will grow old one day and I want to be in a body that can take care of me. Hence I’m taking care of it now. 💝

musicInfo.song_name: Remember the Name (feat. Styles of Beyond)

latestPosts.caption:
Documenting myself/
This day, 5th Oct is the last I remember feeling content and confident in my being. Physically emotionally and mentally at peace, aligned. Peak in a long time. 
Don’t get me wrong, there have been a lot of happy moments around but then there are those special days when your energy flows and you feel aligned, it’s a personal thing with oneself. 
On 9th I fell ill, got dengue, skin broke out, couldn’t go work or work out for a bit, was tired all the time, got lazy, needed a break from social media, needed care, got family time, got stuck in inertia; and now finally today after more than a month, I feel I have the energy again. 
The whimsical mojo is back. Phew.
